node.text:
‘Thank you’ has never been and will never be enough. You pulled us through a number of events, whether you were at the @crossfitgames or watching around the world. Thank you for your encouragement, thank you for giving meaning to this sport, thank you for your loyalty. Training for 2022 has already begun (what’d you expect?). #MayhemInMadison

🎥: @scottvandersloot

node.text: I couldn’t be more excited to announce our new partnership with @threadystate on @mayhemathlete. I’ve been blessed throughout my athletic career with unlimited access to best-in-class experts from a variety of specialities. Our goal with @mayhemathlete is to consolidate the knowledge and experience of these experts in one place to share with you - our community. Over the past 10 years @suppleleopard has helped me with my movement efficiency, training knowledge and injury rehab. More importantly, he has become a great friend and someone I’m excited to introduce to all of you. Alongside his on-ramp, Mayhem Athletes can now expect weekly mobility supplements from Kstarr to accompany our programming. Let’s get to work. #MayhemAthlete #MayhemReady

We had a great day competing at @thelegendsofthefalls for @mayhemmissions. Thank you @reebok, @butcher_box, @roguefitness and our other sponsors for making this special event a possibility. Due to COVID, we kept our awards ceremony virtual but wanted to recognize everyone who completed the course today, it wasn’t easy. Looking forward to next year. 

#butcherboxpartner #reebokathlete #Ryourogue

node.text: I’m not really sure how to start this.  Loyalty is and always has been one of the values I hold strong to and have been anchored in throughout my life.  My personal definition of loyalty takes into account and considers imperfection, making mistakes, asking forgiveness,  and even showing grace to others who can never seem to get it right.  However, my definition of loyalty does have firm boundaries. CrossFit has been something I’ve felt loyalty towards over the past 10 years.  While I’ve struggled with some decisions made by CFHQ over the last couple of years and what I’ve felt like have personally alienated some of the people who sacrificed and helped grow its brand.  That is nothing compared to what has happened the last couple of days and has made it impossible to stay loyal to leadership who make callous statements that alienate and divide in a time when unity is needed.  When I really sit and reflect it hasn’t been CFHQ that I have been loyal to, but the community that supports inclusivity, fitness for all, and health.  We will continue to be a part of that community but can no longer be loyal to someone or something that is so far from my own values.  While I’m considering what our next steps are we cannot and will not stand with these comments or beliefs.

node.text: It is almost impossible to put into words the destruction and devastation that happened here almost a week ago.  This is a video from Tuesday afternoon via @cookevillemayorrickyshelton of one of the neighborhoods that was hardest hit.  I can’t tell you how proud I am of the all of our community leaders, first responders, and volunteers.  Thank you to all of you who have bought shirts and donated, for those who want to continue to help you’ll have a chance @thecrossfitmayhem on Friday night and Saturday morning at Oakland High School.  If you can’t be here in person, there is an opportunity for you to do it in your garage or your local affiliate.  The link in my bio will take you to the sign up and/or donation page where 100% of proceeds will go to those affected by the storm.

Mayhem goes East.. and we’re making @mayhemdesertheat a destination fitness experience you don’t want to miss.

Qualifiers will take place Aug. 13 - Sept. 13. Submit your email at www.mayhemdesertheat.com to get notified about qualifier information. #MayhemDesertHeat

node.text:
@mayhemathlete is offering 30% off (we rarely do this) your first purchase of programming and it ends tomorrow. Use code CHAMPS. We had 50 athletes competing at the @crossfitgames last week and this is the programming all our athletes follow throughout the year, myself included. Link in bio. 

Here’s an idea what you can expect (typically followed by a #mayhemburgenerstrength piece):
3 rounds 
600m run
20 KB swings (70/53)
12 bar MUs
—
4 rounds 
20/16 Cal Echo bike
60 heavy double unders
Rest 1:1
4 rounds
20/16 Cal Echo Bike
20 Bench press (155/105)
Rest 1:1
20/16 Cal Echo Bike
60 heavy double unders
